The Rdio Android SDK lets developers call the web service API, authenticate
users if the Rdio Android app is installed, and play full song streams or
30 second samples.

Full API documentation is available: http://www.rdio.com/media/static/developer/android/docs/

To get started:

Try the sample app and get the source from https://github.com/rdio/hello-android
  - Make sure you uncomment and change the appKey & appSecret to your
    consumer key & secret
Download the Rdio Android API JAR
Download the OAuth Signpost JARs
Add references to the three jars into your Eclipse project
Build & enjoy.
